Title: 500428HP+C Neuropixel style
HPSurgeonComments: Some bleeding occurred during the durotomy, in this case a large blood clot formed from the innervated dura that was the source of the bleed. When lowering the cover slip, this clot (had the appearence of a blood blister of sorts) was compressed and most of the blood trapped in it was squeezed out but there is a large hematoma like spot on the brain. Although i expect this to clear (it is surface level blood), I listed the hematoma as severe due to the size of the spot. I am concerned there is could be some cortex damage just lateral of the center of the window (where the source of the bleed is) but i cannot be sure from the blood in the way, so laceration is listed as mild. ​

Title: 500545HP+C Neuropixel style
HPSurgeonComments: ​The animal was stopped breathing roughly 20 minutes after surgery was completed and was euthanized. A moderate sinus bleed was seen after popping the skull cap. The animals breathing was checked prior to this and was seen to be at a normal rate and intensity.​ The sinus bleed was stopped with gel foam. After the gel foam was removed much darker blood was seen from the site. the breathing rate of the animal reduced in frequency and the iso was reduced to 0 for the remainder of the durotomy. after coveslip was placed the breathing began to pick up and the iso was increased to 4. The rest of the procedure and recovery continued normally until the animal stopped breathing and was euthanized after 10 minutes of the animal not respirating.
